Mongodb TypeError: class heritage events_1.EventEmitter is not an object or null

I'm seeing an issue from the mongodb@5.8.1 npm dependency. I am trying to use mongodb in my Vue.js + Vite + Typescript app but my app crashes and cannot load due to the following error coming from mongodb. I'm not sure why it's trying to resolve events to events_1, I suspect that might be related to this error.

Uncaught TypeError: class heritage events_1.EventEmitter is not an object or null
    js mongo_types.ts:402
    __require2 chunk-AUZ3RYOM.js:18
    js abstract_cursor.ts:16
    __require2 chunk-AUZ3RYOM.js:18
    js aggregation_cursor.ts:11
    __require2 chunk-AUZ3RYOM.js:18
    js collection.ts:6
    __require2 chunk-AUZ3RYOM.js:18
    js change_stream.ts:4
    __require2 chunk-AUZ3RYOM.js:18
    js index.ts:4
    __require2 chunk-AUZ3RYOM.js:18
    <anonymous> mongodb.js:28990
mongo_types.ts:402

Steps to recreate:

  1. npm create vite@latest my-vue-app --template vue-ts
  2. npm install mongodb
  3. Add the following lines into main.ts
import { MongoClient } from mongodb
const client = new MongoClient("")
  1. npm run dev
answer: Yes I understand, but e.g. the `setw` manipulator calls public functions in the stream object (in the case of `setw` it calls [`ios_base::width`](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/io/ios_base/width)). There are simply no way to store special or user-defined data like your time-format in the stream object.
